  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0ddc\u0da0\u0dca\u0da0\u0ddd\u0dbd\u0dda \u0da2\u0db1\u0db1 \u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dba \u0dba\u0dae\u0dcf \u0dad\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dba\u0da7 \u0d9c\u0dda\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0dc3\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0daf\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Two weeks to restore Norochchole generator",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The first generator (Unit 01) of the Lakwijaya Power Plant in Norochchole with a capacity of 300 megawatts has been disabled due to a sudden technical fault. Ceylon Electricity Board says that it is expected to take approximately 02 weeks to restore this generator.",
        "Also, the second (Unit 02) generator of the Lakwijaya power plant is undergoing major overhaul these days, so its total capacity of 300 megawatts has been lost to the national system. Therefore, the national grid has lost 600 megawatts."
      ],
